{"openapi":"3.1.0","info":{"title":"ServiceNow Agent API","description":"ServiceNow AI Agent API with MCP server integration and Redis-based conversation history","version":"1.0.0"},"paths":{"/api/v1/chat":{"post":{"tags":["agent"],"summary":"Chat","description":"Chat endpoint for the ServiceNow agent.\n\nProcesses user instructions using ServiceNow MCP server and maintains\nconversation history via Redis.\n\nSupports OAuth authentication:\n- If OAuth enabled: extracts user context from token\n- If impersonated (OBO): uses OBO token for MCP server calls\n- MCP servers handle ServiceNow token acquisition via JWT Bearer Token flow\n\nHeaders:\n- Authorization: Bearer <azure-ad-token> (required if OAuth enabled)\n\nNote: ServiceNow tokens are obtained by the MCP server using JWT Bearer Token \nflow with user impersonation.","operationId":"chat_api_v1_chat_post","requestBody":{"content":{"application/json":{"schema":{"$ref":"#/components/schemas/AgentRequest"}}},"required":true},"responses":{"200":{"description":"Successful Response","content":{"application/json":{"schema":{"$ref":"#/components/schemas/AgentResponse"}}}},"422":{"description":"Validation Error","content":{"application/json":{"schema":{"$ref":"#/components/schemas/HTTPValidationError"}}}}},"security":[{"HTTPBearer":[]}]}},"/api/v1/approve":{"post":{"tags":["agent"],"summary":"Approve","description":"Approve and resume agent execution after human-in-the-loop interrupt.\n\nThis endpoint is used to provide approval decisions for tool calls that\nrequire human review (e.g., create-incident, update-incident).\n\nThe decisions list must match the order of pending actions from the\noriginal interrupt response.\n\nDecision types:\n- approve: Execute the tool with original arguments\n- edit: Modify the tool arguments before execution\n- reject: Skip executing this tool call\n\nHeaders:\n- Authorization: Bearer <azure-ad-token> (required if OAuth enabled)","operationId":"approve_api_v1_approve_post","requestBody":{